      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Rebuilding Alliance excels in its ability to leverage <cite id=\"10\">non-cash contributions</cite>, which represent a significant portion of its total impact. By focusing on <cite id=\"11\">direct service delivery</cite> in high-urgency areas like Gaza, the organization provides immediate relief such as <cite id=\"5\">hot meals and food parcels</cite> while simultaneously engaging in long-term <cite id=\"12\">legal advocacy to prevent home demolitions</cite>. Their governance is robust, featuring a <cite id=\"13\">90.3% independent board of directors</cite> consisting of seven members."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 2003, Rebuilding Alliance is a dedicated advocacy and relief organization working to <cite id=\"1\">secure equal rights and provide essential humanitarian aid</cite> to Palestinian families. The organization operates at the intersection of <cite id=\"2\">legal advocacy, education, and direct humanitarian support</cite>, focusing on communities in the Gaza Strip, West Bank, and Jerusalem. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $825,817</cite>, which was largely driven by contributions. Despite its relatively small financial footprint compared to global NGOs, it maintains a <cite id=\"4\">90.3% program expense ratio</cite>, ensuring that all reported expenses are directed toward its core mission. Key initiatives include the <cite id=\"5\">Hot Meals Program</cite>, which accounted for over $2.5 million in programmatic activity when including non-cash contributions, and the <cite id=\"6\">Food Parcels Grant</cite> program. Rebuilding Alliance is also known for its <cite id=\"7\">Leadership Learning Missions</cite> and construction projects aimed at helping Palestinian families maintain their land and homes. The organization holds a <cite id=\"8\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, reflecting a high level of public disclosure regarding its goals and strategies.",
